can turn NAs into 0. Also notice that we know have columns Confirmed.x Country_Region.x, Confirmed.y Country_Region.y. So lets rename the Confirmed columns and delete the Country_Region columns

Confirmed_State_3_13_9_13_joined <- full_join(Confirmed_State_3_13,
      Confirmed_State_9_13, by = c("Province_State")) %>% 
      rename(Confirmed_3_13_2020 = "Confirmed.x", Confirmed_9_13_2020 = "Confirmed.y") %>% 
      select(-Country_Region.x, -Country_Region.y) %>% 
      replace_na(list(Confirmed_3_13_2020 = 0))
head(Confirmed_State_3_13_9_13_joined)
## # A tibble: 6 x 3

##MAKING GRAPHS FROM THE TIME SERIES DATA

time_series_long_joined %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region,Date) %>% 
  summarise_at(c("Confirmed", "Deaths"), sum) %>% 
  filter (Country_Region == "US") %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("US COVID-19 Deaths")

time_series_long_joined %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region,Date) %>% 
  summarise_at(c("Confirmed", "Deaths"), sum) %>% 
  filter (Country_Region %in% c("China","Japan", "Korea, South",
                                "Italy","Spain", "US")) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("COVID-19 Deaths") +
    facet_wrap(~Country_Region, ncol=2, scales="free_y")

##Now several countries, same graph

time_series_long_joined %>% 
    group_by(Country_Region,Date) %>% 
    summarise_at(c("Confirmed", "Deaths"), sum) %>% 
    filter (Country_Region %in% c("China","France","Italy", 
                                "Korea, South", "US")) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = Deaths, color = Country_Region)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("COVID-19 Deaths")

can use report_type to show confirmed and deathslog scale works best with low deaths and high confirmed

time_series_long_joined_counts %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region, Report_Type, Date) %>% 
  summarise(Counts = sum(Counts)) %>% 
  filter (Country_Region == "US") %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Date,  y = log2(Counts), fill = Report_Type, color = Report_Type)) + 
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("US COVID-19 Cases")

  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarise(totalDeaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(totalDeaths)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)

time_series_confirmed_US_Province_long<-
  read_csv(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series/time_series_covid19_confirmed_US.csv")) %>% 
  group_by(Province_State, Admin2) %>% 
  select(-c("UID", "iso2", "iso3", "code3", "FIPS", "Lat", "Long_", "Combined_Key", "Country_Region")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-c(Province_State, Admin2),
               names_to = "Date", values_to = "Confirmed") %>% 
  group_by(Province_State, Date) %>% 
  summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed))

time_series_confirmed_US_Province_long %>%
